     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To the Author, Master <hi>Iohn Ford.</hi>
   </head>
   <l>
      <hi>BLacke choler,</hi> Reasons ouer-flowing Spring,</l>
   <l>Where thirsty Louers drinke, or any Thing,</l>
   <l>Passion, the restlesse current of dull plaints</l>
   <l>Affords their thoughts, who deeme lost beauties, Saints:</l>
   <l>Here their <hi>best Lectur<gap reason="illegible: under-inked" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>s</hi> read, collect, and see</l>
   <l>Various conditions of Humanitie</l>
   <l>Highly enlighten'd by thy Muses rage;</l>
   <l>Yet all so coucht, that they adorn'd the Stage.</l>
   <l>Shun <hi>Phocions blushes</hi> thou; for sure to please</l>
   <l>It is no sinne, then what is thy disease?</l>
   <l>Iudgements applause? effeminated smiles?</l>
   <l>Studie's delight? thy wit mistrust beguiles:</l>
   <l>Establisht Fame will thy Physicion be,</l>
   <l>(Write but againe) to cure thy Iealousie.</l>
   <signed>Hum. Howorth.</signed>
</div>
